abstract: Jeanine Cummins’s novel about migrants fleeing violence is a hit with booksellers, but critics have called it “trauma porn” that exploits another country’s pain.

abstract: He broke ground with his assertion that the factors that helped the best companies succeed were also the reasons some of those same companies failed.
snippet: He broke ground with his assertion that the factors that helped the best companies succeed were also the reasons some of those same companies failed.
lead_paragraph: Clayton M. Christensen, a Harvard professor whose groundbreaking 1997 book, “The Innovator’s Dilemma,” outlined his theories about the impact of what he called “disruptive innovation” on leading companies and catapulted him to superstar status as a management guru, died on Thursday in a Boston hospital. He was 67.

abstract: A new comic book series imagines that Nancy has been killed, infuriating some fans of the unstoppable teen detective who made her debut 90 years ago.
snippet: A new comic book series imagines that Nancy has been killed, infuriating some fans of the unstoppable teen detective who made her debut 90 years ago.
lead_paragraph: The Hardy Boys stand over Nancy Drew’s grave. The beloved teen detective, who has survived countless scrapes, cliffhangers and close calls, is dead — or so it seems — killed while pursuing a high-stakes investigation of organized crime. And it’s up to the Hardy Boys to solve the mystery of her murder.

headline_main: Nancy Drew Is Dead! Don't Worry, the Hardy Boys Are on the Case

abstract: Noah Centineo, Lana Condor and hundreds who loved the Netflix rom-com hit walk into a movie theater for the sequel. Cue collective squealing.
snippet: Noah Centineo, Lana Condor and hundreds who loved the Netflix rom-com hit walk into a movie theater for the sequel. Cue collective squealing.
lead_paragraph: Nothing truly bonds hundreds of young women like collectively watching Peter Kavinsky, the swoon-inducing love interest of Netflix’s “To All the Boys I’ve Loved Before” films, do something dashing onscreen — and releasing a wave of ear-shattering screams in unison.

abstract: Secretary of State Mike Pompeo lashed out in anger Saturday at an NPR reporter who accused him of shouting expletives at her after she asked him in an interview about Ukraine. In a direct and personal attack, America's chief diplomat said the journalist had “lied” to him and he called her conduct “shameful.”
snippet: Secretary of State Mike Pompeo lashed out in anger Saturday at an NPR reporter who accused him of shouting expletives at her after she asked him in an interview about Ukraine. In a direct and personal attack, America's chief diplomat said the jour...
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Secretary of State Mike Pompeo lashed out in anger Saturday at an NPR reporter who accused him of shouting expletives at her after she asked him in an interview about Ukraine. In a direct and personal attack, America's chief diplomat said the journalist had “lied” to him and he called her conduct “shameful.”
headline_main: Pompeo Lashes Out at Journalist; NPR Defends Its Reporter
